  "response": "Alright, here's a breakdown of some of the top-rated and/or most successful Hollywood movies of 2017, based on a combination of critical acclaim, box office performance, and general popularity:\n\n**Critically Acclaimed & Award Winners:**\n\n*   **The Shape of Water:** (Guillermo del Toro) - Won Best Picture at the Oscars. Widely praised for its visuals, story, and performances.\n*   **Dunkirk:** (Christopher Nolan) - A tense and immersive war film with stunning visuals and sound design.\n*   **Call Me by Your Name:** (Luca Guadagnino) - A coming-of-age romance that was highly praised for its sensitive portrayal of young love.\n*   **Lady Bird:** (Greta Gerwig) - A charming and relatable coming-of-age story with strong performances.\n*   **Get Out:** (Jordan Peele) - A groundbreaking horror film that tackled social issues in a smart and terrifying way.\n*   **Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri:** (Martin McDonagh) - A darkly comedic drama with strong performances, though somewhat controversial in its themes.\n\n**Box Office Blockbusters:**\n\n*   **Star Wars: The Last Jedi:** (Rian Johnson) - A controversial but hugely successful entry in the Star Wars saga.\n*   **Beauty and the Beast:** (Bill Condon) - A live-action adaptation of the Disney classic that was a massive hit.\n*   **Wonder Woman:** (Patty Jenkins) - A landmark superhero film that was both critically and commercially successful.\n*   **Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2:** (James Gunn) - Another fun and visually impressive Marvel film.\n*   **Spider-Man: Homecoming:** (Jon Watts) - A fresh and entertaining take on the Spider-Man story within the Marvel Cinematic Universe.\n*   **Thor: Ragnarok:** (Taika Waititi) - A humorous and visually vibrant addition to the Thor series.\n*   **Despicable Me 3:** (Pierre Coffin, Kyle Balda, Eric Guillon)\n*   **Justice League** (Zack Snyder)\n\n**Other Notable Films:**\n\n*   **Baby Driver:** (Edgar Wright) - A stylish and energetic action film with a killer soundtrack.\n*   **Logan:** (James Mangold) - A gritty and emotionally powerful superhero film.\n*   **Blade Runner 2049:** (Denis Villeneuve) - A visually stunning and thought-provoking sequel.\n*   **Coco:** (Lee Unkrich, Adrian Molina) - A visually and emotionally rich animated film from Pixar.\n\n**How to Determine \"Top Rated\":**\n\n*   **Metacritic/Rotten Tomatoes:** These sites aggregate reviews from critics and assign a score.\n*   **Awards Recognition:** Films that win major awards (Oscars, Golden Globes, etc.) are generally considered top-tier.\n*   **Box Office Performance:** While not always indicative of quality, significant box office success often suggests a film resonated with a large audience.\n*   **Personal Preference:** Ultimately, what constitutes a \"top-rated\" film is subjective and depends on individual taste.\n\nIt's worth checking out trailers and reviews for these films to see which ones pique your interest! Enjoy your movie watching!",
